\int_0^1 \frac{\ln x}{1+x} \mathrm{d}x=-\int_0^1 \frac{\ln(1+x)}{x}\mathrm{d}x=-\frac{\pi^2}{12}
\int_0^1\frac{\ln x}{x+1}dx=\left[\ln x\ln(1+x)\right]_0^1-\int_0^1\frac{\ln(1+x)}{x}dx=-\int_0^1\frac{\ln(1+x)}{x}dx
\ln(1+x)=x-x^2/2+x^3/3-x^4/4.....
-\int_0^1\frac{\ln(1+x)}{x} dx=-\int_0^1(1-x/2+x^3/3-x^3/4)dx
-\int_0^1(1-x/2+x^3/3-x^3/4)dx=-[1-1/2^2+1/3^3-1/4^2........]
-[1-1/2^2+1/3^3-1/4^2........]=-\pi^2/12
